<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="25" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 810.51/378.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Missions in Argentina, Bolivia,
                                    Brazil, Chile, Colombia, Ecuador, Panama, Paraguay, Peru,
                                    Uruguay</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Secretary of Treasury says: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>In order to arrange program for April meeting of International
                                    High Commission, United States Section earnestly solicits from
                                    each of the other sections early suggestions of questions and
                                    measures requiring immediate consideration and especially a full
                                    and free statement of any changes in United States laws,
                                    regulations and practices that would facilitate closer financial
                                    and commercial relations.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>